; v0.6 value machine — Unit A1: op-param relative writes must read their real
; base via the generic shadow read (read_op_param / drv-player _readParam), not
; the old silent-0. Each :<opparam>+/* below lowers to PARAM_ADD / PARAM_MUL on
; an FM operator field (AR/DR/SR/RR/SL/KS/ML), whose base is the voice value.
; If the read were still silent-0 the Z80 and JS reference would diverge.

(def lead :alg 4 :fb 3
  :ar1 20 :dr1 8 :sr1 2 :rr1 6 :sl1 3 :tl1 24 :ks1 1 :ml1 2 :dt1 0
  :ar2 24 :dr2 10 :sr2 3 :rr2 8 :sl2 4 :tl2 12 :ks2 0 :ml2 1 :dt2 0
  :ar3 22 :dr3 7 :sr3 2 :rr3 6 :sl3 2 :tl3 18 :ks3 0 :ml3 4 :dt3 0
  :ar4 30 :dr4 12 :sr4 3 :rr4 9 :sl4 5 :tl4 6 :ks4 0 :ml4 1 :dt4 0)

(fm1 :tempo 120 lead :oct 4 :len 4 :vel 13
  c :ar1+ 5 e :dr1+ 4 g :rr1+ 3 c
  e :sl1+ 2 g :ml2+ 3 b :sr2+ 4 c
  e :ks1+ 1 g :ar4+ -6 b :dr3* 2 c)
